item.description:
arXiv:2512.24610v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: This paper studies minimizing solutions to a two dimensional Allen-Cahn system on the upper half plane, subject to Dirichlet boundary conditions, \begin{equation*}
  \Delta u-\nabla_u W(u)=0, \quad u: \mathbb{R}_+^2\to \mathbb{R}^2,\ u=u_0 \text{ on } \partial \mathbb{R}_+^2, \end{equation*} where $W: \mathbb{R}^2\to [0,\infty)$ is a multi-well potential. We give a complete classification of such half-space minimizing solutions in terms of their blow-down limits at infinity. In addition, we characterize the asymptotic behavior of solutions near the associated sharp interfaces.
